Which band had you hooked right from the first song you heard from them?

The Moody Blues. Mom and Dad bought an eight-track player (remember those?) when I was about thirteen years old. One of the first tapes they bought was Moody Blues, “In Search of the Lost Chord”. I played that thing to death. I still love it fifty-some years later…it was the Moodies at their peak.

After that, I listened to all of their recordings from the 60s and 70s, and loved them all. I even loved Blue Jays, which was just Justin Hayward and John Lodge while the band was taking its “break”. I’m still a fan.
